Using the column view:
\[
A\vect{x} = 4\begin{bmatrix} 1 \\ 0 \end{bmatrix} + 
(-1)\begin{bmatrix} 2 \\ 3 \end{bmatrix} + 
2\begin{bmatrix} -1 \\ 5 \end{bmatrix}
= \begin{bmatrix} 4 \\ 0 \end{bmatrix} + 
\begin{bmatrix} -2 \\ -3 \end{bmatrix} + 
\begin{bmatrix} -2 \\ 10 \end{bmatrix}
= \begin{bmatrix} 0 \\ 7 \end{bmatrix}
\]

Alternatively, using the **row-vector rule**: multiply each row of 
$A$ by $\vect{x}$ component-wise:
$$
A\vect{x} &= \begin{bmatrix} 
(1)(4) + (2)(-1) + (-1)(2) \\
(0)(4) + (3)(-1) + (5)(2)
\end{bmatrix}
= \begin{bmatrix} 4 - 2 - 2 \\ 0 - 3 + 10 \end{bmatrix}
= \begin{bmatrix} 0 \\ 7 \end{bmatrix}
$$
